 - Check Public IP Address\",\"description\":\"Check your public IPv4, IPv6, ISP and location instantly.\",\"applicationCategory\":\"DeveloperApplication\",\"operatingSystem\":\"Web\",\"browserRequirements\":\"Requires JavaScript\",\"offers\":{\"@type\":\"Offer\",\"price\":\"0\",\"priceCurrency\":\"USD\"},\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"hello-tools\",\"url\":\"https://oxoxox1.com\"}}</script><div class=\"min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-start py-8 px-4\" style=\"background:var(--os9-bg)\"><div class=\"solitaire-accordions mt-6\" style=\"max-width:460px;width:100%\"><div class=\"solitaire-accordion\"><button class=\"solitaire-accordion-header\"><span>How to Use</span><span class=\"solitaire-accordion-icon\">▼</span></button><div class=\"solitaire-accordion-content\" style=\"display:none\"><h2 class=\"text-lg font-bold mb-3\">How to Use the IP Address Checker</h2><div class=\"mb-4\"><h3 class=\"font-bold mb-2\">Step 1: Open the Tool</h3><p class=\"text-sm\" style=\"opacity:0.85;line-height:1.6\">Navigate to this page. Your public IP address is automatically detected and displayed at the top. No clicking needed.</p></div><div class=\"mb-4\"><h3 class=\"font-bold mb-2\">Step 2: Copy Your IP</h3><p class=\"text-sm\" style=\"opacity:0.85;line-height:1.6\">Click the Copy button next to your IP address to copy it to your clipboard. Share it with your network administrator or use it for remote access setup.</p></div><div class=\"mb-4\"><h3 class=\"font-bold mb-2\">Step 3: View Details</h3><p class=\"text-sm\" style=\"opacity:0.85;line-height:1.6\">Check your approximate location, ISP, and network info below the IP address. Click Check Again to refresh the data anytime.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"solitaire-accordion\"><button class=\"solitaire-accordion-header\"><span>Key Features</span><span class=\"solitaire-accordion-icon\">▼</span></button><div class=\"solitaire-accordion-content\" style=\"display:none\"><ul class=\"text-sm list-disc pl-5\" style=\"opacity:0.85;line-height:1.8\"><li>Instant IP detection — no click needed</li><li>Shows IPv4 and IPv6 addresses</li><li>ISP and location info</li><li>One-click copy to clipboard</li><li>100% free, no ads, no signup</li><li>Works on mobile and desktop</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"solitaire-accordion\"><button class=\"solitaire-accordion-header\"><span>Common Uses</span><span class=\"solitaire-accordion-icon\">▼</span></button><div class=\"solitaire-accordion-content\" style=\"display:none\"><ul class=\"text-sm list-disc pl-5\" style=\"opacity:0.85;line-height:1.8\"><li>Check your public IP for remote desktop setup</li><li>Verify VPN or proxy connection</li><li>Troubleshoot network issues</li><li>Share IP with tech support</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"solitaire-accordion\"><button class=\"solitaire-accordion-header\"><span>FAQ</span><span class=\"solitaire-accordion-icon\">▼</span></button><div class=\"solitaire-accordion-content\" style=\"display:none\"><div class=\"text-sm\" style=\"opacity:0.85;line-height:1.6\"><p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Q: <!-- -->What is a public IP address?</strong><br>A: <!-- -->A public IP address is a unique number assigned by your ISP that identifies your device on the internet. It is how websites and services know where to send data back to you.</p><p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Q: <!-- -->Is my IP address visible to websites?</strong><br>A: <!-- -->Yes — every website you visit can see your public IP address. This tool simply shows you what those websites see.</p><p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Q: <!-- -->What is the difference between IPv4 and IPv6?</strong><br>A: <!-- -->IPv4 uses a 32-bit format (e.g., 192.168.1.1) while IPv6 uses 128-bit hex format (e.g., 2001:db8::1). The world is gradually transitioning to IPv6 as IPv4 addresses run out.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"solitaire-accordion\"><button class=\"solitaire-accordion-header\"><span>SEO</span><span class=\"solitaire-accordion-icon\">▼</span></button><div class=\"solitaire-accordion-content\" style=\"display:none\"><p class=\"text-xs leading-relaxed\" style=\"opacity:0.65\">Free online What Is My IP tool. Instantly check your public IPv4 and IPv6 address, ISP, and approximate location. No signup required, works instantly in your browser.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"os9-window mt-8\" style=\"max-width:460px;width:100%\"><div class=\"os9-titlebar\"><span class=\"tracking-[0.5px] text-sm\">How to Use</span></div><div class=\"os9-window-body\"><h2 class=\"text-lg font-bold mb-3\">How to Use the IP Address Checker</h2><div class=\"mb-4\"><h3 class=\"font-bold mb-2\">Step 1: Open the Tool</h3><p class=\"text-sm\" style=\"opacity:0.85;line-height:1.6\">Navigate to this page. Your public IP address is automatically detected and displayed at the top. No clicking needed.</p></div><div class=\"mb-4\"><h3 class=\"font-bold mb-2\">Step 2: Copy Your IP</h3><p class=\"text-sm\" style=\"opacity:0.85;line-height:1.6\">Click the Copy button next to your IP address to copy it to your clipboard. Share it with your network administrator or use it for remote access setup.</p></div><div class=\"mb-4\"><h3 class=\"font-bold mb-2\">Step 3: View Details</h3><p class=\"text-sm\" style=\"opacity:0.85;line-height:1.6\">Check your approximate location, ISP, and network info below the IP address. Click Check Again to refresh the data anytime.</p></div><div class=\"mb-4\"><h3 class=\"font-bold mb-2\">Key Features</h3><ul class=\"text-sm list-disc pl-5\" style=\"opacity:0.85;line-height:1.8\"><li>Instant IP detection — no click needed</li><li>Shows IPv4 and IPv6 addresses</li><li>ISP and location info</li><li>One-click copy to clipboard</li><li>100% free, no ads, no signup</li><li>Works on mobile and desktop</li></ul></div><div class=\"mb-4\"><h3 class=\"font-bold mb-2\">Common Uses</h3><ul class=\"text-sm list-disc pl-5\" style=\"opacity:0.85;line-height:1.8\"><li>Check your public IP for remote desktop setup</li><li>Verify VPN or proxy connection</li><li>Troubleshoot network issues</li><li>Share IP with tech support</li></ul></div><div class=\"mb-2\"><h3 class=\"font-bold mb-2\">FAQ</h3><div class=\"text-sm\" style=\"opacity:0.85;line-height:1.6\"><p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Q: <!-- -->What is a public IP address?</strong><br>A: <!-- -->A public IP address is a unique number assigned by your ISP that identifies your device on the internet. It is how websites and services know where to send data back to you.</p><p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Q: <!-- -->Is my IP address visible to websites?</strong><br>A: <!-- -->Yes — every website you visit can see your public IP address. This tool simply shows you what those websites see.</p><p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Q: <!-- -->What is the difference between IPv4 and IPv6?</strong><br>A: <!-- -->IPv4 uses a 32-bit format (e.g., 192.168.1.1) while IPv6 uses 128-bit hex format (e.g., 2001:db8::1). The world is gradually transitioning to IPv6 as IPv4 addresses run out.</p></div></div></div></div><div class=\"os9-footer\" style=\"max-width:460px;width:100%;font-size:10px;text-align:center;opacity:0.6;margin-top:12px\"><a href=\"/en\" class=\"underline\">Home</a><span class=\"mx-2\">|</span><a href=\"/en/uuid\" class=\"underline\">UUID</a><span class=\"mx-2\">|</span><a href=\"/en/json\" class=\"underline\">JSON</a><span class=\"mx-2\">|</span>hello-tools 2026</div></div><!--$--><!--/$--><footer style=\"text-align:center;font-size:11px;opacity:0.5;padding:16px 0;max-width:640px;margin:0 auto\"><a href=\"/en/about\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:underline\">About</a><span style=\"margin:0 8px\">|</span><a href=\"/en/guide\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:underline\">Guide</a><span style=\"margin:0 8px\">|</span><a href=\"/en/privacy\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:underline\">Privacy</a><span style=\"margin:0 8px\">|</span><a href=\"/en/terms\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:underline\">Terms</a></footer><script>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).p